# Line endings: FreeBASIC sources and resource scripts are CRLF, project-wide.
#
# These were `-crlf` (i.e. `-text`, "store as-is, never convert"). That froze the
# CRLF the T01 sweeps had just established -- necessary at the time, because
# core.autocrlf=true was silently reverting a plain conversion -- but it equally
# froze any LF that arrived afterwards. It preserved the convention without
# enforcing it, and 256 files drifted to LF with no diff noise to warn anyone
# (whole-file rewrites by tooling, and new files simply born LF).
#
# `text eol=crlf` enforces instead of freezing: git normalises to LF in the blob
# and checks out CRLF unconditionally, so a working tree that violates the rule
# is no longer representable. Do not weaken these back to -crlf/-text.
#
# Patterns are repo-wide by design -- a scoped rule is how Templates/ and Tools/
# escaped the original sweeps.

*.bas text eol=crlf
*.bi  text eol=crlf
*.frm text eol=crlf
*.rc  text eol=crlf
